    Combined with <fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-iii-5.2.5"
href="hodge-theory-iii-5.2.5.xml"
number="5.2.5"></fr:ref> and specialised to the case where <fr:tex>S=P^t</fr:tex>, this equation proves <fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-iii-5.2.3.1"
href="hodge-theory-iii-5.2.3.1.xml"
taxon="Equation"
number="5.2.3.1"></fr:ref>.
    In concrete terms, this implies that, to calculate <fr:tex>\mathrm {R} a_*K</fr:tex>, we can proceed in two steps:

    
 <html:ol
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
      
 <html:li
style="list-style-type: &quot;(a) &quot;">
        We take a resolution <fr:tex>K\xrightarrow {\sim } K'</fr:tex> such that the components <fr:tex>F</fr:tex> of <fr:tex>K'</fr:tex> satisfy <fr:tex>\mathrm {R}^i {a_p}_*(F^p)=0</fr:tex> for <fr:tex>i&gt;0</fr:tex>.
        The complex <fr:tex>{a_\bullet }_*K'\in \operatorname {D}^+(S_\bullet )</fr:tex> (the derived category of the category of cosimplicial abelian sheaves on <fr:tex>S</fr:tex>) can be identified with <fr:tex>\mathrm {R}{a_\bullet }_*K</fr:tex>.
      </html:li>


      
 <html:li
style="list-style-type: &quot;(b) &quot;">
        <fr:tex>\mathrm {R} a_*K</fr:tex> is the simple complex <fr:tex>\mathrm {s}{a_\bullet }_*K'</fr:tex> associated to the double complex <fr:tex>{a_\bullet }_*K'</fr:tex>.
      </html:li>

    </html:ol></fr:p><fr:p>
    The spectral sequence <fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-iii-5.2.3.2"
href="hodge-theory-iii-5.2.3.2.xml"
taxon="Equation"
number="5.2.3.2"></fr:ref> generalises to a spectral sequence

